    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 3'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98122' id='8' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='65538' x='33231' y='939'>
            <zone h='98122' id='6' type-v2='layout-basic' w='47230' x='33231' y='939'>
              <zone h='98122' id='5' name='Sheet 2' w='47230' x='33231' y='939'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
            <zone fixed-size='119' h='98122' id='7' is-fixed='true' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='18308' x='80461' y='939'>
              <zone h='10916' id='9' name='Sheet 2' pane-specification-id='0' param='[federated.0y0hy6f17yfws81gdn6ps1g4ym06].[none:Category:nk]' type-v2='color' w='18308' x='80461' y='939'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone h='81808' id='10' type-v2='text' w='18308' x='80461' y='11855'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q5</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>a) Which date level would you choose (Year / Quarter / Month)?</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>I would choose the Month level because it provides detailed trend analysis without being too broad like Year or too detailed like Day.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>b) Why are line charts suitable for time-based analysis?</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>They show trends and patterns over time clearly.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>They help identify growth, decline, and seasonality.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>They make forecasting easier.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone h='98122' id='3' type-v2='text' w='32000' x='1231' y='939'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q4. What insight can be gained by comparing Sales and Profit together? Then explain how you would create a chart to analyze Profit by Sub-Category.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Comparing Sales and Profit together helps identify whether high sales are actually generating profit. A product may have high sales but low profit due to discounts or high costs.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Example Insight:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>A sub-category may generate high revenue but still result in losses, indicating poor pricing or operational inefficiency.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Steps to Create Profit by Sub-Category Chart:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open a new worksheet.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag Sub-Category to the Rows Shelf.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag Profit to the Columns Shelf.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau creates a bar chart automatically.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Sort the chart in descending order to identify the most profitable sub-categories.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Add color to distinguish positive and negative profits if needed.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Result:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The chart clearly shows which sub-categories are profitable and which are loss-making.</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='12' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='98122' id='11' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='97538' x='1231' y='939'>
                <zone h='98122' id='3' type-v2='text' w='32000' x='1231' y='939'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q4. What insight can be gained by comparing Sales and Profit together? Then explain how you would create a chart to analyze Profit by Sub-Category.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Comparing Sales and Profit together helps identify whether high sales are actually generating profit. A product may have high sales but low profit due to discounts or high costs.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Example Insight:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>A sub-category may generate high revenue but still result in losses, indicating poor pricing or operational inefficiency.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Steps to Create Profit by Sub-Category Chart:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open a new worksheet.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag Sub-Category to the Rows Shelf.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag Profit to the Columns Shelf.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau creates a bar chart automatically.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Sort the chart in descending order to identify the most profitable sub-categories.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Add color to distinguish positive and negative profits if needed.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Result:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The chart clearly shows which sub-categories are profitable and which are loss-making.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone fixed-size='280' h='98122' id='5' is-fixed='true' name='Sheet 2' w='47230' x='33231' y='939'>
