    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 4'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98122' id='7' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='97538' x='1231' y='939'>
            <zone h='98122' id='5' type-v2='layout-basic' w='97538' x='1231' y='939'>
              <zone h='49061' id='3' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='939'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q7. Explain the business importance of geographical analysis. Then describe how you would create a Map showing Sales by State using Sample – Superstore</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Business Importance of Geographical Analysis:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Geographical analysis helps organizations:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify high-performing and low-performing regions.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Improve regional marketing strategies.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Optimize supply chain and distribution.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Understand customer demand across locations.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Make location-based business decisions.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Steps to Create a Map Showing Sales by State:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open a new worksheet.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag State to the workspace.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau automatically generates a map because State is a geographical field.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag Sales to the Color Marks card.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Optionally drag Sales to Label for displaying values.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Adjust colors and map style for better visualization.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Result:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>States with higher sales appear darker or larger depending on formatting.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone h='49061' id='8' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='97538' x='1231' y='50000'>
                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='49061' id='9' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='50000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>8. What is the difference between a Worksheet and a Dashboard in Tableau? Why is a dashboard more useful for decision-makers?</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer :</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>A Worksheet </run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>in Tableau is a single chart or visualization used to analyze specific data.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>A Dashboard</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> is a collection of multiple worksheets displayed together on one screen.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Worksheets are used for detailed analysis, while dashboards provide a complete overview using multiple charts, filters, and visuals together.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Dashboards are more useful for decision-makers because they:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Show all important information in one place</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Help identify trends and problems quickly</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Support faster and better business decisions</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Allow interactive filtering and analysis</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Example:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>A worksheet may show only “Sales by Category,” while a dashboard can show sales, profit, region-wise performance, and trends together.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='11' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='98122' id='10' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='97538' x='1231' y='939'>
                <zone h='49061' id='3' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='939'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q7. Explain the business importance of geographical analysis. Then describe how you would create a Map showing Sales by State using Sample – Superstore</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Business Importance of Geographical Analysis:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Geographical analysis helps organizations:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify high-performing and low-performing regions.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Improve regional marketing strategies.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Optimize supply chain and distribution.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Understand customer demand across locations.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Make location-based business decisions.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Steps to Create a Map Showing Sales by State:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open a new worksheet.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag State to the workspace.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau automatically generates a map because State is a geographical field.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag Sales to the Color Marks card.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Optionally drag Sales to Label for displaying values.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Adjust colors and map style for better visualization.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Result:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>States with higher sales appear darker or larger depending on formatting.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
