    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 5'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98122' id='3' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='97538' x='1231' y='939'>
            <zone fixed-size='324' h='98122' id='5' is-fixed='true' type-v2='text' w='51077' x='1231' y='939'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q9.  What is Tableau Prep, and why is it important in real-world data projects? What is Tableau Prep, and why is it important in real-world data projects? Then explain how you would: </run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Remove null values </run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Remove duplicate records</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Change incorrect data types (Answer in steps, no tool access required.)</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau Prep is a data preparation tool used to clean, combine, and transform raw data before analysis in Tableau.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Importance in Real-World Projects:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Improves data quality.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Removes errors and inconsistencies.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Saves analysis time.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Ensures accurate reporting.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Simplifies data transformation.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>(a) Steps to Remove Null Values:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open Tableau Prep and load the dataset.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify fields containing null values.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Click on the null value indicator.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Select Filter Data or Remove Nulls.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The null records are removed from the dataset.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>(b) Steps to Remove Duplicate Records:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Load the dataset into Tableau Prep.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Add a Clean Step.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify duplicate rows using key fields.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Use the Group and Clean options.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Remove repeated records and keep unique values.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>(c) Steps to Change Incorrect Data Types:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open the dataset in Tableau Prep.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Locate the field with incorrect datatype.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Click the datatype icon beside the field name.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Select the correct datatype such as:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>String</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Number</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Date</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Boolean</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone h='98122' id='6' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='46461' x='52308' y='939'>
              <zone h='98122' id='7' type-v2='text' w='46461' x='52308' y='939'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q10. A retail manager wants answers to the following: Which category generates the highest profit? Which region performs poorly? How does sales change over time?</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> a) Mention which charts you would use</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> b) Identify one key insight that management could derive</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> c) Explain how this helps in business decision-making</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Answer:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>(a) Charts Used:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Bar Chart for highest profit category</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Map or Bar Chart for poor-performing region</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Line Chart for sales trend over time</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>(b) One Key Insight:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Technology category may generate the highest profit, while some regions may show lower sales and profit performance.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>(c) Business Importance:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>This analysis helps management improve weak areas, focus on profitable categories, plan marketing strategies, and make better business decisions using data insights.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
